text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia gilbertii is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Pulchellae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and South West regions of Western Australia.The erect slender shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 1.5 metres (1 to 5 ft). It blooms from October to February and produces white flowers.
